# Stakeholder Requirements

## 1. Dealer Principal

### Business Goals

* Increase overall sales revenue.
* Improve lead-to-sale conversion rates.
* Gain visibility into dealership performance.

### Key Requirements

* Real-time sales dashboards.
* Branch-wise performance reporting.
* Lead conversion analytics.
* Revenue forecasting reports.

### Success Criteria

* Increase conversion rate by at least 20%.
* Improve reporting accuracy.
* Reduce lost sales opportunities.

---

## 2. Sales Manager

### Business Goals

* Improve team productivity.
* Ensure timely lead follow-up.
* Monitor sales pipeline performance.

### Key Requirements

* Automated lead assignment.
* Lead prioritization mechanism.
* Sales activity tracking.
* Team performance dashboards.

### Pain Points

* Delayed lead allocation.
* Lack of follow-up visibility.
* Difficulty measuring sales performance.

### Success Criteria

* Reduced lead response time.
* Improved lead conversion ratio.
* Increased sales team efficiency.

---

## 3. Sales Representative

### Business Goals

* Quickly engage potential customers.
* Manage follow-ups efficiently.
* Close more vehicle sales.

### Key Requirements

* Instant lead notifications.
* Centralized customer profiles.
* Test drive scheduling functionality.
* Mobile access to lead information.

### Pain Points

* Manual lead tracking.
* Missing follow-up deadlines.
* Incomplete customer information.

### Success Criteria

* Easy access to lead details.
* Reduced administrative workload.
* Increased number of closed deals.

---

## 4. Marketing Manager

### Business Goals

* Generate high-quality leads.
* Measure campaign effectiveness.
* Optimize marketing spend.

### Key Requirements

* Lead source tracking.
* Campaign performance reporting.
* Lead quality scoring.
* Customer segmentation.

### Pain Points

* Inability to identify top-performing campaigns.
* Limited visibility into conversion outcomes.

### Success Criteria

* Improved campaign ROI.
* Better lead quality measurement.
* Data-driven marketing decisions.

---

## 5. Customer Service Executive

### Business Goals

* Improve customer experience.
* Respond quickly to inquiries.

### Key Requirements

* Access to customer interaction history.
* Lead status visibility.
* Automated reminders.

### Pain Points

* Limited visibility into customer journey.
* Inconsistent communication.

### Success Criteria

* Faster customer responses.
* Improved customer satisfaction scores.

---

## 6. IT Administrator

### Business Goals

* Ensure system reliability.
* Support integrations and data security.

### Key Requirements

* Secure user access controls.
* Integration with dealership systems.
* Data backup and recovery mechanisms.

### Pain Points

* Multiple disconnected systems.
* Data inconsistencies.

### Success Criteria

* Stable system performance.
* Reduced maintenance effort.
* Successful system integrations.

---

## 7. Regional Operations Manager

### Business Goals

* Standardize dealership operations.
* Monitor branch performance.

### Key Requirements

* Common lead management process.
* Branch-wise reporting.
* Operational KPI dashboards.

### Pain Points

* Process inconsistencies across branches.
* Limited operational visibility.

### Success Criteria

* Standardized workflows.
* Improved branch performance monitoring.

---

# Stakeholder Power-Interest Matrix

## High Power, High Interest

* Dealer Principal
* Sales Manager
* Marketing Manager
* Regional Operations Manager

Management Strategy:
Engage regularly, involve in decision-making, and obtain approval for major requirements.

## High Power, Low Interest

* Executive Leadership

Management Strategy:
Provide periodic updates and key project milestones.

## Low Power, High Interest

* Sales Representatives
* Customer Service Executives

Management Strategy:
Gather feedback frequently and involve in user acceptance testing.

## Low Power, Low Interest

* Customers

Management Strategy:
Monitor satisfaction and collect feedback through surveys.

